				\begin{document}$$G = \tau_{{\rm{trap}}}^{e,h}/\tau_{{\rm{transit}}}^{h,e}$$\end{document}At VTG = 0 V, there is no p channel and thus photogenerated holes remain trapped, either in the bulk of the semiconducting blend or at the dielectric-semiconductor interfaces4, leading to photoconductive gain. The photocurrent is largest when the channel is accumulated with electrons (VBG = 20 V), at which the photogenerated electrons are strongly amplified. Figure 2d shows the intensity dependence of the photocurrent and the corresponding photo-responsivity (defined as R=Iphoto∕PinA\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
